<P>
   MEDIA-BUSINESS
</P>
<P>
   (Coding varies.)
</P>
<P>
   NARROWCAST-TV-MEDIA (Los Angeles) _ The proliferation of niche
cable channels like E! Entertainment in recent years has turned the
old economic model for success on its head. While broadcast
networks battle to attract big audiences with expensive
programming, so-called narrowcast channels have been building
highly profitable businesses by thinking small and keeping
programming budgets tight. In fact, much of E!'s programming, like
movie trailers and highlights from the daily TV talk shows, comes
at virtually no cost. By James Sterngold.
</P>
<P>
   PHILLY-PAPER-MEDIA (Undated) _ A look at the tense relations
between the Philadelphia Inquirer, a former reporter and the
archdiocese. By Felicity Barringer.
</P>
<P>
   CSPAN-BOOKS-MEDIA (Undated) _ CSpan2 launches
all-weekend-programming about books. A look at how the station has
become a player in the marketing of books. By Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
