<P>
   TECH-STOCK-STARTUPS (Undated) _ After a month of hot and heavy
flirting about a prospective merger, last Monday was going to be
the day that CKS Group and USWeb finally got serious and set the
price. Then the stock market started falling, dragging with it the
already depressed shares of both companies. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 7 p.m. ET in ``f'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center display)
</P>
<P>
   NARROWCAST-TV-MEDIA (Los Angeles) _ As a new television season
approaches, the broadcast networks are winding up an annual rite
that involves spending hundreds of millions of dollars developing
new series in hopes of finding the next ``Seinfeld'' or ``E.R.''
But don't expect to see this sort of exercise on the niche cable
channels, like E! Entertainment, which often succeed by spending
far more modest sums and attracting relatively small but loyal
audiences. By James Sterngold.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic is being sent to NYT graphics clients.
Non-subscribers can make individual purchase by calling (888)
603-1036 or (888) 346-9867.)
