<SLUG> BC-TV-FALL-THURSDAY-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHAT'S NEW THIS FALL ON THURSDAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JOHN LEVESQUE  
 c.1998 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here is a look at the new TV shows on Thursday this fall. Check
local listings for times, channels.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jesse
</P>
<P>
   NBC
</P>
<P>
   Kelly Bundy has a brain!
</P>
<P>
   Oops, wrong show.
</P>
<P>
   Jesse Warner has a brain, which is nice for Christina Applegate,
who played the witless Kelly Bundy on ``Married . . . With
Children'' for 11 seasons. In ``Jesse,'' Applegate plays a smart,
devoted, hard-working single mom who is so overwhelmed by
responsibility that she refuses to make time for herself.
</P>
<P>
   Though the pilot episode of ``Jesse'' has its amusing moments,
it offers nothing particularly special. And producers
Bright/Kauffman/Crane (``Friends,'' ``Veronica's Closet'') were
retooling the pilot and making cast changes to find the right
chemistry before foisting it on the masses. So, as they say in TV
land, stay tuned.
</P>
<P>
   _ Vengeance Unlimited
</P>
<P>
   ABC
</P>
<P>
   Introducing the new venge-o-matic! He slices around the law, he
dices with danger, he doubles as judge and jury.
</P>
<P>
   His name is Mr. Chapel, but there's nothing sacred about his
occupation. He gets even when the justice system gets it wrong. If
a terrorist has murdered your family but goes free on a
technicality, Mr. Chapel is the go-to guy _ a wily trickster who'll
bring the miscreant to justice any way he sees fit. Only one catch:
It'll cost a million bucks, or you'll owe Mr. Chapel a favor down
the road.
</P>
<P>
   Designed to appeal to the baser human instincts, ``Vengeance
Unlimited'' is a perfectly cynical counterpoint to CBS's ``Promised
Land,'' one of its Thursday night competitors. Michael Madsen stars
as Mr. Chapel, a mysterious man who has apparently been hideously
wronged by the system. We don't know exactly why or how, but it's
clear that his capacity for retribution makes him one sick puppy.
</P>
<P>
   Lending a hand and making sure that Mr. Chapel doesn't wax too
wacko is paralegal KC Griffin (Kathleen York), a former beneficiary
of Chapel's services who works for the district attorney and has
access to helpful information on baddies who've gone free or
goodies who've been wrongly accused.
</P>
<P>
   She could wash her hands of Mr. Chapel after doing him one
favor, but there's something that keeps her coming back for another
sting operation. Maybe it's her thirst for justice, maybe it's his
English Leather.
</P>
<P>
   Whatever the attraction, this isn't a show for children, even
though ABC is putting it on at 8 o'clock. And if you know of any
adults who end up liking ``Vengeance Unlimited,'' make sure you've
returned everything you borrowed from them.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hollyweird
</P>
<P>
   Fox
</P>
<P>
   Fox announced in January that ``Hollyweird'' would be on its
fall schedule, but production was delayed so the producers could
revise the concept. And now comes word that Fox won't put it on the
air any earlier than midseason, and possibly not at all.
</P>
<P>
   That could be a bad sign. Or it could be a good sign. It
certainly is a sign that the first attempt to deliver a finished
product didn't work out so well. Fox decided to go back to the
drawing board and recast the show after reaction to the initial
concept was less than enthusiastic.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hollyweird'' is described as a ``quirky noir/gothic show''
from Wes Craven and Shaun Cassidy about a trio of undercover cops
in Los Angeles, originally hand-picked by the LAPD for a
reality-based TV series. The police department scrapped plans for
the TV show, but kept the unit intact to probe the ``wild,
glamorous and often scary'' world of Hollywood.
</P>
<P>
   While the fate of ``Hollyweird'' is debated, Fox is likely to
fill the Thursday night time slot with the summer series ``Guinness
World Records,'' another in its seemingly endless reservoir of
reality shows.
</P>
<P>
   RETURNING THURSDAY SHOWS
</P>
<P>
   ``Diagnosis Murder''
</P>
<P>
   ``ER''
</P>
<P>
   ``48 Hours''
</P>
<P>
   ``Friends''
</P>
<P>
   ``Promised Land''
</P>
<P>
   ``Veronica's Closet''
</P>
<P>
   ``World's Wildest Police Chases''
</P>
<P>
   EXISTING SHOWS MOVING FROM THURSDAY
</P>
<P>
   ``20/20'' to Wednesday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   EXISTING SHOWS NEW TO THURSDAY
</P>
<P>
   ``For Your Love.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Frasier.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Jamie Foxx Show.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Steve Harvey Show.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Wayans Bros.''
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY SHOWS GONE FOR GOOD
</P>
<P>
   ``Ask Harriet''
</P>
<P>
   ``Between Brothers''
</P>
<P>
   ``Cracker''
</P>
<P>
   ``413 Hope St.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Living Single''
</P>
<P>
   ``Nothing Sacred''
</P>
<P>
   ``Prey''
</P>
<P>
   ``Seinfeld''
</P>
<P>
   ``Union Square''
</P>
