<HEADLINE>
(HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
 AM-SPORTS-NYT-BUDGET
<TEXT>
<P>
   Add N.Y. Times News Service budget for papers of Monday, Sept.
7:
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   (Coded s)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-CARDINALS-REDS (St. Louis) _ Reds vs. Cardinals. By Murray
Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-CUBS-PIRATES (Pittsburgh) _ Chicago vs. Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-HOMERUN-BALL-TAXES (Pittsburgh) _ If a fan catches the ball
that breaks baseball's home run record, and generously gives it to
the slugger, it could be more than a great baseball event. It could
be the taxable event of a lifetime. Fans attending games featuring
Mark McGwire and Sammy Sosa might want to buy extra tickets for
their accountants. According to the Internal Revenue Service, the
bleacher bum who paid $6 to $10 for a ticket _ not the
multi-millionaire slugger _ could owe federal gift tax. For a fan
giving a million-dollar ball to McGwire or Sosa, the tax could
reach $150,000 or more. The person receiving a gift owes no tax.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-WHITESOX (Chicago) _ New York vs. Chicago. By Buster
Olney.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-BRAVES (New York) _ New York vs. Atlanta. By Jason
Diamos.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-CURRY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports column on Braves-Mets. By
Jack Curry.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-DIANA (Saratoga Springs, N.Y.) _ The Diana at Saratoga. By
Joseph Durso.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JETS-49ERS (San Francisco) _ Jets vs. San Francisco. By
Gerald Eskenazi.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-GIANTS-REDSKINS (East Rutherford, N.J.) _ Giants vs.
Redskins.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports column on
Giants-Redskins. By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-USOPEN (Undated) _ Action at the U.S. Open. By Robin Finn.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-BERKOW-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports column on Monica Seles. By
Ira Berkow.
</P>
