</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   SAPELO _ For the first time in 120 years, the Sapelo Island
Light will reach out over the sea and surrounding estuaries,
capping several years work and a $300,000 investment. Officials
Sunday will dedicate the historic lighthouse, which has been
restored and refurbished. Ceremonies Sunday evening will feature a
dramatic night-time lighting. (Seabrook, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   LABORDAY-CAMPAIGN _ Though it's traditionally considered the
start of the fall political season, Georgia politicos will be doing
little campaign labor on that day. With the advent of media driven
campaigns, old fashioned barbeques and parades culminating in
rallies on the courthouse square on national holidays have given
way to ratings points and carefully crafted 30-second scripts that
really haven't stopped since the July 21 primaries. We take a look
at what the top tier candidates are doing and what politicos and
such have to say about how the races will shape up from here
entering the homestretch of the campaign. (Pruitt, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
