</P>
<P>
   NY-YOUTH-MARCH (New York) _ The aftermath of the Million Youth
March: the mayor says the city kept the peace, organizers say
otherwise. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   AFGHAN-IRAN-ASSESS (Cairo, Egypt) _ Although all-out war appears
unlikely, the tens of thousands of Iranian troops deployed in a
threatening buildup along the Afghan border have drawn attention to
the hostility between two of the world's most conservative Islamic
governments. By Douglas Jehl. (The story has moved in ``i'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   ATTACK-TANZANIA (Dar es Salaam, Tanzania) _ Investigators have
arrested two more suspects in the bombing of the U.S. Embassy here
and have made significant progress in determining how the bomb was
made and taken to the embassy, FBI and local police officials say.
By James C. McKinley Jr. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-SUIT (Undated) _ A look at the legal cases that
Microsoft and the government are likely to present, based on their
witness lists. By Steve Lohr. (The story has moved in ``f'' news
file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
