u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBN-BRAVES-ONDECK07-C     09-06 0267
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-BRAVES-ONDECK07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On Deck: New York Mets
 &HT;    By Jack Wilkinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 1:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Shea Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: Fox Sports South; 750 AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Denny Neagle (14-11, 3.69 ERA;
5-3, 4.05 lifetime vs. Mets) vs. RHP Masato Yoshii (5-8, 3.91; 0-2,
8.39 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Neagle makes his 31st start, in search of his fourth
straight win. Since losing 1-0 at Los Angeles Aug. 16, he's beaten
the Dodgers, Cards and, most recently, the Astros last Tuesday in
Atlanta. Neagle gave up 10 hits and four earned runs that night in
the Braves' 6-4 victory. Part of his recent success: While Neagle
has been tagged for a team-high 25 homers, he has allowed just one
in his last three starts. He's 1-0 in two starts this year against
the Mets; he went seven no-decision innings in an 11-inning, 3-2
win July 5 at Turner Field, then easily beat Yoshii at Shea 12-1 on
July 15 (six innings, four hits, one run). The Mets' Butch Huskey
and Brian McRae have each homered twice off Neagle in the past,
while John Olerud (4-for-10, 1 HR) and Mike Piazza (9-for-24)
usually hit him well. In losing his two starts against Atlanta,
Yoshii gave up 16 hits and 11 runs (nine earned) in just 9 2/3
innings. On July 15 at Shea, he lasted just 3 2/3 innings,
surrendering seven earned runs on nine hits, including homers to
Andres Galarraga and Ryan Klesko. Collectively, the Braves are
batting .400 (16-for-40) against Yoshii.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
