<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BANGLADESH-FLOODS (Chor Shibola, Bangladesh) _ More than 20
million Bangladeshis have had their homes swamped by monsoon-season
flooding, that so far has lasted twice as long as any other
recorded. The waters have inundated more than half of the country,
killed more than 520 people, shut down many roads, damaged more
than 4,000 schools, wiped out a big chunk of the main rice crop and
now threaten to bring deadly diseases. The prime minister, Sheik
Hasina Wazed, has pleaded for international relief. By Celia S.
Dugger.
</P>
<P>
   (Locator map has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
