approaches, the broadcast networks are winding up an annual rite
that involves spending hundreds of millions of dollars developing
new series in hopes of finding the next ``Seinfeld'' or ``E.R.''
But don't expect to see this sort of exercise on the niche cable
channels, like E! Entertainment, which often succeed by spending
far more modest sums and attracting relatively small but loyal
audiences. By James Sterngold.
