<P>
   (NYT5) NEW YORK -- Sept. 6, 1998 -- MOVING-MUSICIANS, 9-6 --
Susan Salm, a musician with the Raphael Trio, pushing her cello
into a taxi in Manhattan. Ms. Salm, who travels quite extensively,
knows the intricacies of moving her large instrument across
continents and oceans perhaps a bit too well. For thousands of
musicians who, like Salm, play instruments larger than a piccolo,
just getting from point A to point B can be quite an adventure.
(Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
